2:Given a number 
N
N and an array 
A
A of 
N
N numbers. Determine if it's palindrome or not.

Note:

An array is called palindrome if it reads the same backward and forward, for example, arrays { 1 } and { 1,2,3,2,1 } are palindromes, while arrays { 1,12 } and { 4,7,5,4 } are not.




ANS:

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int N;
    cin >> N;

    int A[N];
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        cin >> A[i];
    }

    for (int i = 0; i < N / 2; i++) {
        if (A[i] != A[N - 1 - i]) {
            cout << "NO";
            return 0;
        }
    }

    cout << "YES";
    return 0;
}
